  "prompt": "Why don't some people like cats?",
  "response": "People may dislike cats for various reasons:\n\n1. Allergies\n- Cat hair and dander can cause allergic reactions\n- Some people are highly sensitive to cat allergens\n\n2. Personality differences\n- Cats are often less social and more independent than dogs\n- Some people prefer more interactive and responsive pets\n\n3. Behavioral concerns\n- Cats can scratch furniture\n- Litter box maintenance\n- Potential for spraying or marking territory\n\n4. Negative past experiences\n- Previous bad interactions with cats\n- Traumatic encounters or fear from childhood\n\n5. Cleanliness perceptions\n- Concerns about cats walking in litter boxes and then on surfaces\n- Perception of cats being less clean than other pets\n\n6. Cultural or personal preferences\n- Some cultures view cats differently\n- Individual comfort levels with animal behaviors\n- Personal pet preference\n\n7. Unpredictable nature\n- Cats can be less predictable in their moods\n- Some people find their behavior harder to understand\n\n8. Potential property damage\n- Scratching furniture\n- Knocking over objects\n- Potential home accidents\n\nThese reasons vary by individual and aren't universal, as many people love cats for their unique qualities and companionship.",
